<div id='paymentSection'>

	<div class='headlineQuestion'>How do you prefer to pay the deposit for this order?</div>
	<div class='modestHeadlineText'>(Deposit: ${{#to_fixed order.pricing.depositAmount 2}}{{/to_fixed}})</div>

	<div id='paymentOptionSection' >
		<span class='regularRadioInput'>
			<input id='creditCardOption' type='radio' name='paymentMethod' value='cc'/><label for='creditCardOption'>Credit Card</label>
		</span>
		<span class='regularRadioInput'>
			<input id='checkOption' type='radio' name='paymentMethod' value='c'/><label for='checkOption'>Check</label>
		</span>
	</div>

	<div id='paymentMethodSeparator' class='separator'></div>

	<div id='checkMessage'>
		<p>
			Please keep in mind that (unless stated otherwise in our terms of agreement above) a check for ${{#to_fixed order.pricing.depositAmount 2}}{{/to_fixed}} 
			before the job begins. The rest of the balance will be collected either in phases or in lump sum when 
			our work is complete.
		</p>
		<p>
			We will not begin the job until we receive the check. In order to pay by check, you must mail the check to:
		</p>

		<span id='mailingAddress'>
			<span>2 Technology Drive, Suite 4569</span>
			<span>Warren, NJ, 07059</span>
		</span>
	</div>

	<div id='creditCardSection'>

		<div class='sectionHeadline'>Your Credit Card Details</div>

		<div class='specialMessageSection'>
			<span>
	            <i class='fa fa-exclamation-circle'></i>
			</span>
			<p>
				You will only be paying ${{#to_fixed order.pricing.depositAmount 2}}{{/to_fixed}} today. The rest of 
				the balance will be paid either in phases or in lump sum once we finish the job to your satisfaction.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div id='creditCardNumberContainer' class='formRow'>
			<span class='controlGrouping'>
				<label for='creditCardNumber'>Credit Card Number</label>
				<input type='tel' id='creditCardNumber' maxlength='16' />
			</span>
				<span id='ccMerchantsAccepted'>
				<i id='visaCCIcon' class='fa fa-cc-visa'></i>
				<i id='mastercardCCIcon' class='fa fa-cc-mastercard'></i>
				<i id='discoverCCIcon' class='fa fa-cc-discover'></i>
				<i id='amexCCIcon' class='fa fa-cc-amex'></i>
			</span>
		</div>

		<div id='creditCardSecurityInfo' class='formRow'>
        <span class='controlGrouping'>
            <label for='expirationDateMonth'>Expiration Date</label>
            <span class='controlGroupingRow'>
                <select id='expirationDateMonth' >
                    <option value='' selected='selected' disabled>Month</option>
                    <option value='1'>January</option>
                    <option value='2'>February</option>
                    <option value='3'>March</option>
                    <option value='4'>April</option>
                    <option value='5'>May</option>
                    <option value='6'>June</option>
                    <option value='7'>July</option>
                    <option value='8'>August</option>
                    <option value='9'>September</option>
                    <option value='10'>October</option>
                    <option value='11'>November</option>
                    <option value='12'>December</option>
                </select>
                <select id='expirationDateYear' >
                    <option value='' selected='selected' disabled>Year</option>
					{{#each expirationYears }}
						<option value='{{this}}'>{{this}}</option>
					{{/each}}
                </select>
            </span>
        </span>
			<span class='controlGrouping'>
            <label for='securityCode'>Security Code</label>
            <span class='controlGroupingRow'>
                <input type='tel' id='securityCode' maxlength='4' />
                <span id='creditCardSecurityCodeHelp' data-tooltip-position='right middle' data-tooltip='<div class="tooltipMedium">The security code is either 3 or 4 digits that stand out on the back of your card.</div>'>
                    <i class='fa fa-question-circle'></i>
                </span>
            </span>
        </span>
		</div>
	</div>

</div>